### Order API Endpoints

@baseUrl = https://localhost:7000/api/orders

### Get all orders
GET {{baseUrl}}

### Get order by ID (using query parameter)
GET {{baseUrl}}?id=1

### Get order by ID (using path parameter - still available)
GET {{baseUrl}}/1

### Get order by order number (using query parameter)
GET {{baseUrl}}?orderNumber=ORD-20250818-1234

### Get orders by customer email (using query parameter)
GET {{baseUrl}}?customerEmail=john.doe@example.com

### Get orders by status (using query parameter - 0=Pending, 1=Processing, 2=Shipped, 3=Delivered, 4=Cancelled, 5=Refunded)
GET {{baseUrl}}?status=1

### Create a new order
POST {{baseUrl}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "customerName": "John Doe",
  "customerEmail": "john.doe@example.com",
  "totalAmount": 129.99,
  "status": 0,
  "notes": "Customer requested express delivery"
}

### Update an order (using query parameter)
PUT {{baseUrl}}?id=1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "customerName": "John Doe Updated",
  "customerEmail": "john.doe@example.com",
  "totalAmount": 149.99,
  "status": 1,
  "notes": "Updated order amount and status"
}

### Update order status only (using query parameter)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}?id=1
Content-Type: application/json

2

### Check if order number exists (using query parameter)
GET {{baseUrl}}/exists?orderNumber=ORD-20250818-1234

### Delete an order (using query parameter)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}?id=1
